Help in debugging issues



---

8. Retry Mechanism


---

When Retry is Allowed

Condition	Action

Status = NACK	Retry allowed
No response received	Retry allowed



---

When Retry is Blocked

Condition	Action

Status = ACK	Retry blocked
Already successfully sent	Retry blocked



---

How Retry Works

System re-evaluates conditions

XML is regenerated

TAR file is resent



---

Purpose

Ensure failed transactions are processed successfully

Avoid unnecessary retries



---

9. Closure Logic


---

Objective

Ensure that once a transaction is completed in Conserto, it is also closed in Connexis.


---

Trigger

User clicks Completed button



---

Conditions

Connexis transaction ID exists

Connexis status = ACK

Track & Trace has been sent at least once



---

Process

1. Generate final XML


2. Create TAR file


3. Send to Connexis


4. Update final status




---

Result

Transaction is fully synchronized

Both systems reflect the same final state



---

10. Special Scenario – Throwback Handling


---

Scenario

User may send event back to a previous stage (e.g., MO)


---

Problem

System may resend already sent status



---

Solution

Before sending:

Check history table



---

Rule

If status already sent successfully → Do NOT resend



---

Impact

Prevents duplicate updates

Maintains data consistency



---

11. End-to-End Response Flow

Send → Connexis Processing → Response Received → XML Parsed → DB Updated → Retry / Closure


---

12. Real-World Scenarios


---

Scenario 1: Successful Flow

Data sent → ACK received → Process complete



---

Scenario 2: Failure

Data sent → NACK received → Retry triggered



---

Scenario 3: No Response

Data sent → No response → Retry



---

Scenario 4: Duplicate Prevention

Status already sent → No resend



